        <name>37.2.3.1 Tyre burst, mountain-bike rider</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The probability that a mountain-bike rider travelling along a certain track will have a tyre burst
is {@p_tyre@}. Find the probability that among {@n_riders@} riders:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;exactly one has a burst tyre: [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;at most three have a burst tyre: [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;two or more have burst tyres: [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; please round your answer to the nearest \(3\) decimal places.&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;SOLUTION:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Binomial distribution \(\text{P} (X=r)=\&amp;nbsp; ^n\!C_rp^r(1-p)^{n-r}\) where \(p\) is the probability of single `success' which is `tyre burst'.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;\(\text{P} (X=1)=\  ^{{@n_riders@}}\!C_1({@p_tyre@})^1({@1-p_tyre@})^{{@n_riders -1@}}={@ta_1@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="math display"&gt;\(\begin{aligned}
\text{P} (X\le 3)&amp;amp;=\text{P} (X=0)+\text{P} (X=1)+\text{P} (X=2)+\text{P} (X=3)\\
&amp;amp;=({@1-p_tyre@})^{{@n_riders@}}+{@n_riders@}({@p_tyre@})({@1-p_tyre@})^{{@n_riders - 1@}} \\ &amp;amp; \qquad+ \frac{{@n_riders@}\times {@n_riders-1@}}{2\times 1}({@p_tyre@})^2({@1-p_tyre@})^{{@n_riders - 2@}}\\
&amp;amp;\qquad +\frac{{@n_riders@}\times {@n_riders-1@}\times {@n_riders-2@}}{3\times 2\times 1}({@p_tyre@})^3({@1-p_tyre@})^{{@n_riders-3@}} \\ &amp;amp; ={@ta_2@}\end{aligned}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;\(\begin{aligned}&amp;nbsp;\text{P} (X\ge 2)&amp;amp;=1-\text{P} [(X=0)\cup (X=1)] \\ &amp;amp; = 1-({@1-p_tyre@})^{{@n_riders@}}-{@n_riders@}({@p_tyre@})({@1-p_tyre@})^{{@n_riders - 1@}} \\ &amp;amp;= {@ta_3@}\end{aligned}\)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
